<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-01 16:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Beheads Drug-smuggler, Murderer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia today
beheaded an Indian drug smuggler and a convicted Saudi murderer, a
report reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
The official Saudi Press Agency quoted an Interior Ministry's
statement as saying that the Indian who was identified as Margoub
Hussein Abdel Majeed was beheaded after found guilty by a
religious court in Saudi Red Sea coastal city of Jeddah.
</P>
<P>
He was arrested earlier this year while trying to smuggle
heroin and hashish into the Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
The sentence came three days after Saudi Arabia beheaded an
Indian and an Afghan on similar charges.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the statement said that Hamid Bin Hamed Al-Maleki,
a Saudi national, was beheaded after he was convicted of
shooting and killing his compatriot Khaled Bin A'Aeth Al-Maleki
after a squabble.
</P>
<P>
The execution raised to 89 the number of people beheaded in
Saudi Arabia so far this year.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia strictly applies the Islamic Sharia law and
beheads convicted murderers, drug smugglers, rapists and other
criminals with the sword.
</P>
<P>
A record 191 people were executed in the Islamic Kingdom in
1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
