<HEADLINE> Chauffeur of Diana Was Drunk: Paris Public Prosecutor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The chauffeur who crashed the
car carrying Diana Spencer, her friend Egyptian billionaire Dodi
Al Fayed and her bodyguard Saturday night was found to have an
over high rate of alcohol in his blood.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse quoted Paris Public Prosecutor's office as
saying today that the chauffeur, who was only identified as "Mr.
Paul", was apparently drunk when he crashed the car into a pillar
in a downtown Paris underground tunnel.
</P>
<P>
The chauffeur, the former wife of the British crown prince, and
the Egyptian billionaire died in the incident, while the fourth
man in the car, Trevor Rees-Jone, is being treated in hospital.
</P>
<P>
"Analysis of his blood revealed a rate of alcoholic
impregnation of punishable nature," said a communique issued by
the Paris Public Prosecutor's office.
</P>
<P>
The blood of the chauffeur contained 1.75 grams of alcohol,
while the law only allows 0.5 grams of such intoxicant, said the
communique.
</P>
<P>
After the fatal incident took place, many people blamed several
photographers, who tried by snap pictures of Diana with her friend
by pursuing the car on motocycles, for the death of the princess.
</P>
<P>
But both the French government and judicial departments have
called for caution in determining the exact cause of the incident.
</P>
<P>
"The investigations have been given to determine the context
of the pursuit and for appreciate the behavior of the driver of
the car, in order to know in which way he could have been blocked
or influenced in his move not only by the pursuing vehicles but
also but any other circumstance," said the communique.
</P>
<P>
Police have detained seven photographers who were involved in
the pursuing of Diana after she left a luxurious hotel in central
Paris Saturday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
