<HEADLINE> S. Arabia Receives British-Made Minesweeper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia received
today the third British-made minesweeping ship under a
multi-billion-dollar agreement between the two countries, reports
reaching here from Saudi western coastal city of Jeddah said.
</P>
<P>
The minesweeper named "His Majesty's Al-Kharj" arrived in
Jeddah after a month-long journey from Britain's Southampton Port
where it was manufactured and will join the Saudi Royal Navy.
</P>
<P>
The ship, equipped with modern mine-detecting and destruction
devices, is the third of its kind Saudi Arabia ordered from
Britain under the second phase of the 14-billion-pound sterling
(about 23-billion-U.S.-dollar) Al-Yamamah Defense Pact signed by
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement stipulates that Britain supplies Saudi Arabia
with highly sophisticated military equipment including Tornado
jets and minesweepers in two phases.
</P>
<P>
The first phase was executed in 1985, while the second, which
took effect in 1993, stipulated the provision of three such
state-of-the-art minesweepers to Saudi Arabia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
