<DOCNO> XIE19970902.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-01 17:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran's Supreme Leader Against US Cultural Dominance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Supreme Leader Ali
Khamenei today warned against U.S. attempts to dominate the world
intellectually and culturally.
</P>
<P>
Addressing officials in charge of Iranian culture abroad,
Khamenei said, "gone is the time for application of military and
political methods or economic sanctions aimed at dominating the
world."
</P>
<P>
He said that a nation's identity is characterized by its
culture, adding that Westerners try to dictate their criteria and
standards to other countries.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian leader warned that the West's cultural assault
should be taken seriously. "This assault against the Islamic
system and the regions which the West deems dangerous is very
serious although this has not been understood well," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that if the West sees all officials in this country
reject the Western culture, it will realize that it is at odds
with the Islamic system.
</P>
<P>
He said "this explains why the West is constantly urging the
Islamic system to return to the world community while it really
means that the system should accept the culture of the West."
</P>
<P>
Observers here said Khamenei's statement sounds a tough warning
that Iran will not undergo dramatic changes in politics and
culture under the relatively moderate President Mohammad Khatami,
who was sworn in August 4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
