<HEADLINE> Israeli Police Arrests 8 Palestinian Protesters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Israeli police and security
forces arrested eight Palestinian protesters this afternoon at the
Jordan Valley, according to Jerusalem Media and Communication
Center (JMCC) based in east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Several hundred Palestinian farmers conducted today a sit-in at
Al-Fara'h Agricultural Testing Station in the Jordan Valley to
protest against Jewish settlers' raid on the station on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Warning that the station and its nearby area is a military
zone, Israeli security forces and police entered the station this
afternoon to disperse the farmer protesters. During the clashes
between the two sides, eight protesters were arrested.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Jawad Saleh, minister of agriculture of the Palestinian
National Authority who led the protest, said that the Jewish
settlers were preparing to plant and farm at Al-Fara'h area on
Sunday but the Palestinian farmers were not allowed to do so.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian farmers therefore decided to stage the
demonstration, he said. 
</P>
