<HEADLINE> Tanzanian President Stresses All-round Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian President Benjamin
Mkapa today stressed all-round education approach not merely
passing of examination in schools.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a function in a secondary school in Dar es Salaam,
Mkapa said that schools should not try to program a machine that
passes examinations and instead strive to produce educated and
socially well developed human beings.
</P>
<P>
He noted, "Some of our schools provide narrow-based education, an
education geared principally to passing examination and not the
all-round development of the academic, artistic, physical, social,
psychological and personality profile of the students."
</P>
<P>
Mkapa in his speech also called on non-governmental institutions
and the private sector to participate in providing education to the
children, saying, "Preparing our children for tomorrow's world by
providing them with a good solid education is too heavy a stask to
be shouldered by the government alone."
</P>
<P>
He said that anyone with means and possibility to play an active
part is welcome and greatly encouraged to promote education of
children for a better Tanzania tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
