<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Saint Lucia Establish Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- China and Saint Lucia issued
a joint communique today on the establishment of diplomatic
relations at ambassadorial level.
</P>
<P>
The communique said that the two governments have agreed to
develop friendly relations between the two countries on the basis
of the principles of mutual respect for sovereignty and
territorial integrity, mutual non-aggression, non-interfence in
each other's internal affairs, equality and mutual benefit, and
peaceful coexistence.
</P>
<P>
"The Government of Saint Lucia recognizes that there is but one
China in the world, that the Government of the People's Republic
of China is the sole legal government of China and that Taiwan is
a province of the People's Republic of China, " said the
communique.
</P>
<P>
China expressed support for Saint Lucia in its lofty cause of
maintaining national independence and state sovereignty and
developing its national economy.
</P>
<P>
The two governments agreed, in accordance with the provisions
of the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic Relations of 1961 and
international practice, to exchange ambassadors as soon as
possible and to provide each other on a reciprocal basis, with all
the necessary assistance for the establishment of embassies in
their respective capitals, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
Saint Lucia is a tiny island country in the West Indies, one of
the Windward Islands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
