<HEADLINE> Unidentified Attacker Kills 4 in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Four people were killed and two
others wounded today when an unidentified attacker opened fire
indiscriminately in northern Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The gunman went into a shooting spree, firing bullets into
crowds attending a funeral in the northern governorate of
Qalyubia, about 60 kilometers north of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
Security officials rushed to the scene of the attack, and a
hunt is under way for the culprit.
</P>
<P>
An Interior Ministry official, judging from preliminary
investigations, ascribed the shooting to a family feud.
</P>
<P>
Feudal vendetta has been blamed for a large number of deadly
crimes in Egypt, which is a closely-knotted Muslim society.
