<HEADLINE> Five People Killed in Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Five people on a sky-diving
flight were killed in a crash at Bremerton National Airport in
Washington state Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Associated Press said today the victims, four men and a woman,
were on board of the single-engine Cessna 182, which crashed into
a ravine and burst into flames at the airport.
</P>
<P>
The plane took off just before 4:30 p.m. local time (0830 GMT),
then seemed to have engine trouble and apparently tried to turn
back to the airport.
</P>
<P>
Airport officials said the pilot made no radio calls before the
crash. The National Transportation Safety Board was to begin its
investigation today.
</P>
<P>
Less than five hours later, several people were injured when
the nose gear of an Alaska Airlines jet collapsed after it landed
at Seattle-Tacoma International Airport.
</P>
<P>
The collapse forced the 111 passengers and five crew
members aboard the jet to exit by emergency slides. Several people
were taken to hospital with minor injuries, the Federal Aviation
Administration said. 
</P>
