<HEADLINE> Russia, ABS Sign Cooperation Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Russia and the Asian Bankers
Association (ABS) signed a cooperation accord in Moscow today.
</P>
<P>
The accord deals with the rules of exchanging information and
the communication of experience in banking business, banking
security and legislation on banking business, the Inter-fax News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accord will promote contact and communication between
bankers of Russia and Asia, Inter-fax quoted a Russian official as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin attended the opening
ceremony Monday of the two-day ABS conference, which was held in
Russia for the first time, and appealed to the banks in the
Asian-Pacific region to increase their investments in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin sent a letter of
congratulations to the 14th ABS conference expressing hope of
further cooperation between Russian and foreign banks.
</P>
<P>
The association, founded in 1981, consists of more than 200
major banks in the Asian-Pacific region. Two Russian banks are to
join the ABS later this year. 
</P>
