<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto today stressed the importance of Japan-China ties,
saying that "the stable development of bilateral relations between
Japan and China is extremely important to peace and prosperity in
the Asian-Pacific region and the world at large."
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto spoke to a group of Chinese journalists ahead of his
four-day official visit to China starting Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It is a good time now for the two countries to enhance
bilateral ties as this year marks the 25th anniversary of the
normalization of diplomatic relations between Japan and China and
next year is the 20th anniversary of the signing of the
Japan-China Peace and Friendship Treaty, Hashimoto said.
</P>
<P>
He said he will exchange views frankly with Chinese leaders on
the development of bilateral ties with a view towards the 21st
century, and promote the two countries' friendly cooperation in
various fields when he visits China.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that Japan will cooperate with China in as many
fields as possible, not only on bilateral issues, but also on
international issues, in the future.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto added that it is also important to deepen mutual
understanding and promote trustful relations between the two
peoples, especially between the young people of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto will visit Beijing and two northeastern Chinese
cities, Shenyang and Dalian, on September 4-7 to commemorate the
25th anniversary of the normalization of Japan-China diplomatic
ties.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, Hashimoto is scheduled to meet Chinese President
Jiang Zemin, Premier Li Peng and other government officials.
</P>
