<HEADLINE> IOC Suspends Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The International Olympic
Committee (IOC) Tuesday suspended Ecuador from the Olympic
movement.
</P>
<P>
The IOC is not satisfied with the way Ecuador is running its
National Olympic Committee (NOC).
</P>
<P>
The IOC had talked with the country's IOC member Agustin Arroyo
and announced the suspension.
</P>
<P>
The IOC said in a statement that it was "in the best interest
of the Ecuadorian sport movement and its athletes in particular."
</P>
<P>
The decision will not stop athletes from Ecuador taking part in
international events at the moment. But it may prevent the
country having a say in the running of international sport and
could affect the IOC funding they receive. 
