assigned officials at the Montheriya crossing to handle entrance
procedures for Iranian visitors, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Communication, mail, health and banking services at the
Montheriya crossing are in order, said the report. And rest
houses, parking lots, a restaurant and a free market have also
been provided for Iranians, it added.
</P>
<P>
Iraq last month notified Iran that it would lift its travel ban
on Iranian pilgrims imposed since the 1980 when the eight-year
Iran-Iraq war broke out and would allow them to visit Shiite
Muslim shrines on its territory. The lifting will be effective on
September 4.
</P>
<P>
But Iran has dismissed the Iraqi offer and said it was
ambiguous and attempting to divert attention from unresolved
issues between the two countries, such as prisoners of war. Iran
argued that both sides should negotiate on the conditions of the
travelling of Iranians to Iraq. 
