<HEADLINE> Mongolia's International Reserves Jump </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's international
reserves doubled in the first eight months of this year to an
eight-year high, the central bank said today.
</P>
<P>
The huge rise, from 60 million U.S. dollars in January to 120
million dollars to date, was mainly due to the central bank's
purchase of gold, the country's trade surplus and a stable
currency in the eight months, the head of the bank said.
</P>
<P>
The central bank bought 4,000 kilograms of gold in the first
seven months and expected to double the purchase by the end of
this year. Exports increased in the first half of this year and
exceeded imports by 20 million dollars, the official said. 
