<HEADLINE> Five Chinese Nurses Get Nightingale Medal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin
presented the Nightingale Medal to five Chinese nurses today at a
ceremony organized by the Chinese Red Cross Society.
</P>
<P>
The medal is the highest international award for nurses and is
named after Florence Nightingale, the well-known pioneer in
nursing. It was established by the International Red Cross Society
in 1925, and is presented every two years to 50 of the world's
outstanding nurses.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Red Cross Society began to recommend candidates for
the award in 1983, and since that time 22 Chinese nurses have been
recognized with it.
</P>
<P>
