<HEADLINE> Legal Proceedings Open against Photographers in Diana Tragedy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Paris Public Prosecutor today
began legal proceedings for ``involuntary homicide and injury''
against seven photographers.
</P>
<P>
The French photographers who pursued the car of the late British
Princess of Wales Diana Saturday night in Paris.
</P>
<P>
The car crashed into a pillar in an underground tunnel in
downtown Paris after speeding 180 kilometers per hour, killing
Diana, Egyptian billionaire Dodi Al Fayed and the driver, and
seriously injuring the bodyguard of Diana.
</P>
<P>
The photographers were tailing the car on speeding motorcycles,
which are very common in Paris.
</P>
<P>
The Paris Investigation Judge Herve Stephan also charged the
photographers with ``non assistance to person in danger,'' as they
continued to take photos after the car crashed throwing Diana out of
the cabin, according to witnesses.
</P>
<P>
The photographers, whose identities were not given, have been
detained by police since the accident took place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
