<HEADLINE> New Air Route to Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China Southern Airlines will
open an air route from Beijing to the city of Brisbane in
Australia, via Guangzhou, capital of south China's Guangdong
Province, on September 21.
</P>
<P>
This is the 30th international air route on China Southern's
charts. The airline will open two flights, on Thursday and Sunday,
with return trips on the following day. The air distance between
Guangzhou and Brisbane is over 7,200 kilometers, with a travel
time of more than eight hours, the airline said.
</P>
<P>
The new route will help economic, cultural and trade exchanges
between the two countries, authorities said.  
