<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Germany to Conduct Joint Naval Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian and German
navies will conduct a joint exercise aimed at forging closer ties
in defence relations.
</P>
<P>
The exercise, codenamed "DESEX 972", will be held to coincide
with the four-day visit of four German warships to Malaysia from
September 4.
</P>
<P>
About 650 German navy personnel and three Royal Malaysia Navy
(RMN) ships will take part in the two-day exercise beginning on
September 7, German Ambassador to Malaysia Harald N. Nestroy said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Nestroy said the exercise, the first such exercise between an
European country and a Southeast Asian nation, would enable both
navies to exchange experiences to face future international task
such as peacekeeping operations.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia and Germany are part of the international peacekeeping
force serving in Bosnia-Herzegovina.
</P>
<P>
The four Germany warships already visited Israel and India
before coming to Malaysia and are also expected to sail to
China, South Korea, Japan, the Philippines, Brunei, Indonesia and
Egypt before returning home on December 5. 
