<HEADLINE> Illegal Liquor Left 40 Dead in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- More than 40 people died and
at least 100 others fell ill after drinking illegally distilled
liquor in Batticaloa District of Eastern Province, Sri Lanka,
according to informed sources here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The sources said these people were dead after drinking liquor
purchased from several liquor shops in Kalawanchikudi.
</P>
<P>
police sources said 45 people were killed and a group of others
were seriously ill.
</P>
<P>
Two liquor store owners have been taken into custody by police
for questioning, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
It was the highest number of the casualties in a single
incident of liquor poisoning in recent years in the country.
</P>
<P>
The sources also said police suspect that Tamil rebels may be
involved in poisoning the liquor. Investigations are continuing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
