<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ARPC-6 Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Regional Conference
of the World Federation of United Nations Associations (ARPC-6)
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Li Peng and UN Secretary General Kofi Annan
sent messages to the conference, which was sponsored by United
Nations Association of China, one of the founding members of the
federation.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen spoke at
today's opening ceremony, elaborating on China's view on the
international situation, the cooperation in the Asia-Pacific
region and the reform of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the ceremony, Qian also met with leaders of the World
Federation of UN Associations (WFUNA) and representatives from the
UN associations of 16 Asia-Pacific countries.
</P>
<P>
Topics of the conference include the cooperation in the
Asia-Pacific region, strengthening the influence of Asia-Pacific
countries in the United Nations and the role of UN associations in
regional economic, social and cultural cooperation.
</P>
<P>
WFUNA is the sole non-governmental international organization
created to support the UN.  
</P>
</TEXT>
