<HEADLINE> Share Prices Remain Low on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Despite their marginal rise,
share prices remained low on the Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index rebounded by 9.8 points to close
at 1796.24 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 260.08 million units, worth
550.46 million Singapore dollars (about 364.54 million U.S.
dollars). Declines continued to overwhelm advances by 294 to 73
while 239 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Magnum Corporation was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 18.23 million units. It was followed by
Ber Group which had 17.05 million shares traded. Super Coffeemix
was next with 12.32 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
BMT 100 led the gainers of the day as it surged by 10 dollars
to finish at 100 dollars. Jardine M Holdings 400 rose by 90 cents
to end at 7.5 U.S. dollars while Cerebos gained 42 cents to close
at 4.7 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, YTL Corporation was the biggest loser as it
declined by 3.12 dollars to close at 2.38 Singapore dollars.
Rashid Hussain fell by 1 dollar to finish at 3.32 Singapore
dollars and Elec was 80 cents lower ending at 6.7 U.S. dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
