<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Agricultural Conference Opens in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- A five-day international
conference on agriculture opened here today with the aim of
safeguarding the agricultural development in the dry areas in
West Asia and North Africa.
</P>
<P>
The conference brought together about 60 participants from
Algeria, Iraq, Jordan, Lebanon, Libya, Morocco, Syria and Tunisia.
</P>
<P>
The Participants also include delegates from regional and
international research institutions and organizations working in
the fields of agriculture, natural resource management and policy
formulation.
</P>
<P>
The conference - the International Conference on Agricultural
Growth, Sustainable Resource Management and Poverty Alleviation
in the Low Rainfall Areas of West Asia and North Africa - is
aimed at making contribution to balanced agricultural growth and
food security in the countries of West Asia and North Africa
regions, according to a statement released by one of the
organizers - the International Center for Agricultural Research
in Dry Areas.
</P>
<P>
The aim will be realized through the formulation of strategies
for sustainable resource management and poverty alleviation in
the low rainfall areas in the context of market liberalization,
the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The conference is organized by the Jordanian National Center
for Agricultural Research and Technology Transfer, the
International Food Policy Institute and the German Foundation for
International Development.
</P>
<P>
It is co-sponsored by the International Fund for
Agricultural Development and the Arab Fund for Economic and
Social Development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970902.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ronaldo to Miss Italian Cup Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Ronaldo will have to skip the
Inter Milan's Italian Cup debut against Foggia slated for
Wednesday night due to injury.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Brazilian twisted his left knee in the end of
Sunday's match, in which Inter won 2-1 over Brescia.
</P>
<P>
Team doctor Piero Volpi said that Ronaldo would be back on top
form after three or four days of rest.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo's next game will be against Roberto Baggio's Bologna on
September 14.
</P>
<P>
Inter Milan will finally decide on Thursday how much they will
pay Barcelona for the Brazilian striker. After the two clubs
failed to reach an agreement, the matter is to be settled by
football's ruling body FIFA at a meeting in Cairo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
