<HEADLINE> Five Chinese Girls Qualify for Individual Apparatus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Five Chinese women gymnasts
qualified for the finals of individual events at the 1997 World
Gymnastics Championships after the qualifying round competitions
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the rules of the championships, eight leading
gymnasts in each of the four apparatus of vault, uneven bars,
beam, and floor exercise will go into the finals, but only two
from each team will be allowed to compete in the finals. With
points in each of the four events added up, 36 leading women will
compete in the individual all-round final, but only three from
each team are allowed.
</P>
<P>
Of the six Chinese gymnasts including Bi Wenjing, Kui Yuanyuan,
Liu Xuan, Meng Fei, Mo Huilan and Zhou Duan competing on Monday
evening in the qualifying round, five have qualified for the
individual finals.
</P>
<P>
Kui Yuanyuan, Liu Xuan, and Meng Fei will compete in the
individual all-around competition on September 5; Kui Yuanyuan and
Zhou Duan will compete in the vault final on September 6; Meng Fei
and Mo Huilan in the uneven bars final on September 6; Kui
Yuanyuan in the beam final on September 7; Meng Fei and Zhuo Duan
in the floor exercise final on September 7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
