<HEADLINE> 4 Soldiers Killed in East Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- At least four government
soldiers were killed and three others injured in fighting this
morning with Tamil rebels in Eastern Province of Sri Lanka,
according to military sources here.
</P>
<P>
The sources said a group of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) rebels engaged troops at a patrol base with small
arms at Kahawattamunai in Batticaloa District around 6:20 am
today.
</P>
<P>
The troops fought back with small arms and light machine guns.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been waging a war for a separate state in the
north and east of the country since 1983.  
</P>
