<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Youth Conference Taps Business Opportunity in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Junior Chamber
International (JCI), a worldwide youth organization, opened its
annual summit here today with the theme of "Hong Kong -- A gateway
to Develop Business in China".
</P>
<P>
More than 200 delegates from 80 junior chambers around the
world have flown to Hong Kong to attend the four-day event,
including seminars, meetings with government officials and
businessmen, visits to factories in Hong Kong and three southern
Chinese cities -- Zhongshan, Guangzhou and Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong became a natural choice as the venue for this year's
summit because of its return to China on July 1, and the potential
consumer market and robust economic growth in the inland areas,
according to the organizer, the Hong Kong Junior Chamber (HKJC),
an affiliated member of the JCI.
</P>
<P>
Henry U, HKJC's president, said today: "This is a great
opportunity for us to get the message across to the young people
around the world that Hong Kong continues to function as a dynamic
business and financial center and that the city will benefit
greatly from its strengthened links with the rest of China."
</P>
<P>
Inaugurated in 1950, HKJC is an association of young people
aged between 21 and 40, who in their spare time work for the
betterment of the community.
</P>
<P>
JCI, which helps the youth develop leadership skills and social
responsibility, has affiliated chambers all over the world with a
combined membership of 400,000. Every year it holds an annual
summit in different cities to focus on a different theme.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970902.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
