<HEADLINE> Kazakh FM Praises China in New Book </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan's Foreign Minister
Kasymzhomart Tokayev spoke highly of China's achievements over
recent years in his new book.
</P>
<P>
Tokayev also praised China in the newly-published book entitled
"Under the Flag of Independence" as his country's good neighbor
and important partner.
</P>
<P>
By adhering to the foreign policy of independence and peace, he
said, the Chinese government has been playing an increasingly
influential role in Asian affairs.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders stand for maintaining social and political
stability while working on economic reforms, and for strengthening
the Communist party's leadership, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The recent five years have seen China's gross national product
growing by an average 11 percent a year, inflation down, people's
living standards improving, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
With the country's foreign reserves increasing to over 100
billion U.S. dollars, China now enjoys higher ratings on the
international credit market, Tokayev said. 
</P>
