<HEADLINE> OIC Greets Ramos on Anniversary of Signing Mindanao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of the Islamic
Conference (OIC) today congratulated Philippine President Fidel
Ramos on the first anniversary of the signing of a peace accord
between Manila and a major Muslim rebel force in the country.
</P>
<P>
Exactly one year ago, the Philippine government and the Moro
National Liberation Front (MNLF) signed a historic peace accord in
Manila, ending a 24-year-long bloody war between the MNLF and
government forces in Mindanao, the southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
In a message from Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, where the OIC is based,
Azeddine Laraki, OIC secretary general, said he saluted the
"highly laudable" efforts, courageous sacrifices and concessions
by both Ramos and MNLF chairman Nur Misuari that resulted in the
successful conclusion of the peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Laraki said the peace process was conducted under the auspices
of the OIC Ministerial Committee of Six, chaired by Indonesia and
also composed of Libya, Saudi Arabia, Senegal, Somalia and
Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Laraki said that the OIC has always advocated a peaceful, just,
comprehensive and lasting solution to the problem of the southern
Philippines "within the framework of the sovereignty of the
Philippine government."
</P>
<P>
In an earlier message, Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali Alatas
also paid tribute to Ramos for his "vigorous and constant" support
for the implementation of the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Alatas said the full implementation of the peace agreement will
be another important contribution of the Philippines to the
stability and progress in Southeast Asia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
