<HEADLINE> Polish Commemorate World War II </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Polish people from all walks of
life today joined various activities to commemorate the 58th
anniversary of the outbreak of World War II.
</P>
<P>
In the Polish capital, representatives from the government, the
Warsaw province, the Warsaw city and veterans' groups laid wreaths
at the tomb of the unknown soldiers.
</P>
<P>
On Westerplatte Peninsula of Gdansk, veterans, residents and
foreign delegates held a memorial meeting in front of the Monument
to the Coastal Protector.
</P>
<P>
At the dawn of September 1, 1939, Nazi German troops launched a
blitz attack on the Polish army in Westerplatte Peninsula and thus
the European part of World War II began.
</P>
<P>
After over a month of resistance, the Polish army surrendered.
And throughout the war, some 6 million Polish people, or one sixth
of the population, died. 
</P>
</TEXT>
