<HEADLINE> Shanxi Sets up Special Fund for Handicapped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- A special fund has been set up
in North China's Shanxi Province for its handicapped population
living in poverty.
</P>
<P>
The fund was established by Shanxi's Handicapped Union and the
Handicapped Welfare Fund. 100,000 yuan (about 12,000 US dollars)
was donated last Saturday alone.
</P>
<P>
There are 1.34 million handicapped people in Shanxi, 800,000 of
whom live in the rural areas and 100,000 in impoverished
circumstances.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government of Shanxi has made painstaking
efforts in recent years to help improve the living conditions of
its handicapped population, but the under-developed economy in the
province has greatly deterred the process.  
</P>
</TEXT>
