<HEADLINE> S. Lebanon Brush-fire Incident Claims Fifth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The brush fire which
killed four Israeli soldiers last Thursday in South Lebanon
claimed fifth victim Monday, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
Shumato Kasahoun, 21, died late Monday in Haifa's Ramban
Hospital from the serious injuries he suffered in the blaze
following heavy fighting with gunmen from the Amal Shiite
movement in the eastern sector of the Israeli-claimed South
Lebanon Security Zone.
</P>
<P>
Four Israeli soldiers were burned to death on the hill slope
and six others wounded, three seriously, when they were caught
in the middle of a fierce brushfire caused by the fighting.
</P>
<P>
Israeli News Agency Itim has reported that the blaze, which
quickly spread and engulfed the squad of soldiers on an ambush
duty, was in fact caused by the "friendly fire."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Israeli army investigators continued their probe
into the cause of the unprecedented incident.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai is to convene late today a
meeting of senior commanders to discuss the incident and aid to
the northern communities, which are under constant threat of
attacks from anti-Israeli guerrilla forces in South
Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
