<HEADLINE> Gene Treatment Center Set up in Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China's first gene treatment
center has been established in this capital city of northwest
China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The center was sponsored by a research institute studying the
application of gene diagnosis technology in medical treatment
under the No.4 Military Medical University of the People's
Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
Using a microscopic enlargement of just a drop of blood or
saliva, or a single strand of hair, researchers can detect a
bacterium, a virus or a cancer cell and more accurately diagnose a
patient's condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
