<HEADLINE> Hi-Tech Industry Grows in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The hi-tech industry in east
China's Anhui province had 20.2 billion yuan (2.46 billion US
dollars) in output value from 1992 to 1996, 2.35 billion yuan
in pretax profits, and 240 million US dollars in foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
Local officials attributed this to government efforts to use
research developments in production.
</P>
<P>
Hi-tech industrial development zones in the cities of Hefei,
Wuhu and Bengbu are playing a major role in this field.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of the year, the output value of the Hefei
Hi-Tech Development Zone reached 2.23 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
