<HEADLINE> First Car Leasing Chain Company Starts Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China's first car leasing
chain company opened Monday, with its first outlet established
near the city's airport.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Shijitong Auto Club also plans to set up outlets in
Shanghai, Xi'an, Guangzhou, Shenzhen and 31 other major cities in
the country by the end of this year, Guo Jiyuan, the firm's
president announced here in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing outlet, which has more than 30 Santana cars, also
started selling membership cards yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Guo said that the company is computerized, enabling club
members to register in one city and rent cars at a price below the
market level in other cities.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 300 car leasing companies in China,
including over 200 in Beijing. However, they restrict their
service only in cities where they are based. Beijing has over half
a million people with driving licenses but without their own cars.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
