<HEADLINE> Old Chinese Industrial Base Looking for Overseas Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Overseas funds could be a
major factor in developing the economy of Xiangtan City, an old
industrial base in south China's Hunan province, Mayor Jiang
Jianguo told Xinhua recently.
</P>
<P>
He said that overseas funds could help fund construction
projects and get the city more involved in the global economy.
</P>
<P>
He said: "We have asked all departments to fully implement the
preferential policies made by the central, provincial and
municipal governments."
</P>
<P>
Xiangtan has 2.7 million people and is near the hometown of
late Chairman Mao Zedong. It has 58 big state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"At present, when the lack of funds hinders development, I
believe overseas investors will find many chances to succeed in
Xiangtan," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of the year, the city had 20.5 percent
more funds than in the same period last year, and its total
industrial output and income of overseas-funded enterprises
increased by 10.7 percent and 8.2 percent respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
