<HEADLINE> Xiamen Customs Offers Convenience to Credible Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Xiamen Customs has decided to
provide preferential treatment to 38 leading export and import
enterprises in going through customs procedures.
</P>
<P>
The customs of Xiamen, located by the Taiwan Straits, named 24
enterprises eligible for simplified customs procedures in 1995,
thus setting a national precedent.
</P>
<P>
On August 29, the customs signed a memorandum with local
enterprises under which it renewed or offered the favorable
policies to 38 enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"The move is in line with the need to build a modern customs
system suitable for a socialist market economy," a Xiamen customs
official said. 
