<HEADLINE> ADB Helps Manila Improve Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) has approved a 0.15 million U.S. dollar grant to help the
Philippine government prepare a Manila air quality improvement
project.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here today, the Manila-based bank said
that the grant will be used to examine important elements of an
urban air quality management strategy, which has been developed by
an inter-agency institution comprising government agencies,
international organizations, non-governmental organizations and
the private sector.
</P>
<P>
With the grant, it said, the Philippine government will review
proposals for introducing a motor vehicle inspection system,
assess the capacity building, enforce air quality regulations and
analyze strategies required to mitigate deteriorating air quality
in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
Studies show that Manila's air pollution has become
increasingly serious with total suspended particulates often
reaching five times the maximum tolerable limit established by the
World Health Organization. 
</P>
