<HEADLINE> Floods Kill 20 People in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Floods triggered by heavy
rains have hit six counties in Romania, killing at least 20 people
over the past few days.
</P>
<P>
The State Agricultural Department today said the floods have
drowned 590,000 hectares of farmland so far this year and caused
damage equivalent to 108 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The crop land for wheat suffered most heavily with 230,000
hectares affected nationwide, the government agency said.
</P>
<P>
Besides human casualties, said the Romanian news agency
ROMPRES, nearly 30,000 homes and hundreds of businesses, as well
as communications and transportation systems, have been inundated.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasters in the country were quoted as saying that
more rains are expected in the days to come. 
</P>
