<HEADLINE> Encyclopedia of Chinese Literature Published in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The Encyclopedia of Chinese
Literature, the largest and most authoritative reference book on
the development and achievements of Chinese writings for almost
3,000 years, has been published in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
It took hundreds of experts on Chinese literature and culture
over a decade to compile the encyclopedia.
</P>
<P>
The book contains more than five million Chinese characters. It
traces the history of Chinese literature back to before the Qin
Dynasty (221-207 BC), when China became a unified nation.
</P>
<P>
It consists of 12 sections, covering topics ranging from folk
literature, ethnic literature, literary theory and criticism, and
literary history, and has some 18,000 entries, including those of
some 6,400 prominent writers and 8,000 excerpts of their works.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
