<HEADLINE> 226 Die of Cholera in Tanzania's Lindi Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-three people
died of cholera last week, bringing the total deaths to 226 for
the last four months in Tanzania's Lindi Region.
</P>
<P>
The local press today quoted Regional Medical Officer Marcus
Kalinga as saying on Monday that the disease has infected 2,758
people in his region.
</P>
<P>
Kalinga attributed the spread of the disease to the use of
contaminated water.
</P>
<P>
He said that although the region in collaboration with the
Department of Water is taking steps to treat the water, the only
solution to the problem is for the users to boil drinking water
and adhere to hygienic rules. 
</P>
