<HEADLINE> Plant Symbols Chosen in East China Fujian Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The coastal Chinese province of
Fujian recently named the banyan and the daffodil as its official
tree and flower symbols based on a poll taken in the region.
</P>
<P>
The results showed that among the four types of trees listed
for consideration by experts, the banyan won 82.4 percent of the
votes while the daffodil won 84.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The banyan, a kind of fig trees which bear small fruit, is quite
popular in eastern China. Its Chinese name "Rong" is another name
for Fuzhou, the provincial capital, said an official.
</P>
<P>
"The choosing of a province tree and flower will promote
environmental protection in the province," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
