<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Makes Achievements in Producing Robots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China has produced intelligent
robots as advanced as those made by developed countries thanks to
new discoveries in technological research, according to scientists
from the Fifth Robotics Symposium.
</P>
<P>
Some universities and research institutes in China have
developed several kinds of intelligent robots with automatic
functions by adopting multi-sensors to handle information and
program the robot's capabilities. Among the new robots are the
"auto navigation mobile robot" made by the Shenyang Institution of
Automation, the "shopping guide robot" by Shanghai University, the
"automatic car" by Qinghua University and the tourism guide by the
Harbin Polytechnical University.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 experts across the country attended the symposium held
at Harbin Polytechnical University last week, discussing space
robots, robot dynamics, intelligent control and other robotic
technology.
</P>
<P>
"The industrialization of robot production has aroused great
concern among scientists, and the development in cloning
technology has led to discussion on basic topics in robotics,"
said Cai Hegao, vice-chairman of the symposium.
</P>
<P>
Cai, who is also director of the Robotics Institute in Harbin
Polytechnical University, added that China's robotics research has
made rapid progress and will have a bright future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
