<HEADLINE> China Builds Yellow River Theme Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 2 (Xinhua) -- A Yellow River theme park
opened Monday in Zhengzhou, capital of central China's Henan
Province, where the river runs through.
</P>
<P>
The park features a man-made 3.7-kilometer Yellow River as well
as many duplicated historical sites and relics along the river,
including terra cotta figures and Buddhist temples.
</P>
<P>
The Yellow River, the second longest in China after the
Yangtze, is known as the cradle of the Chinese civilization. Many
dynasties built capitals along the river.
</P>
<P>
However, it became less attractive in the 1990s, with its lower
section drying up every year as a result of drought, seriously
affecting millions of people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
