<HEADLINE> WB Supports Indonesia's Clean River Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank (WB) has agreed
to donate 8 billion rupiah (about 2.6 million U.S. dollars) to
Indonesia to support its clean water program, official sources
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank assistance would be allocated to developing
1,000 low cost and very low cost houses along the Karang Mumus
River in Kalimantan, Indonesia, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
There are 2,591 families planned to be removed from the Karang
Mumus areas.
</P>
<P>
It takes about 20 billion rupiah (around 6.6 million U.S.
dollars) to finance the housing project. The remaining cost would
be drawn from the budget of the local government.
</P>
<P>
The housing project is expected to be completed before the
Sixth Five-Year Development Plan (1994-1999).  
