<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Tamil Rebels Search for Deserters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels of
the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) are in search of
deserters from its cadres in the Batticaloa district in the East.
</P>
<P>
According to Tamil sources today, at least seven members of the
LTTE had deserted in the district Friday.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has launched a hunt for them and informed all camps in
the area to be on the lookout for them as they could surrender to
the government forces and divulge vital information.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 30 men and women cadres are being held in Batticaloa
district for attempting to desert.
</P>
<P>
Two other senior cadres who were financial controllers in
Batticaloa and had deserted with LTTE funds are also on the
rebel's wanted list. 
</P>
