<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Upgrade Coal Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China is making efforts to
upgrade its township and village to guarantee a healthy
development of the industry.
</P>
<P>
Today's "China Daily" quoted Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo as saying
that one key way is to construct better coal mines in some 200
counties.
</P>
<P>
Information from the Ministry of Coal Industry revealed that it
would give priority to building and upgrading mines in the 200 key
coal-producing counties.
</P>
<P>
According to the same sources, the ministry and China
Agricultural Bank have jointly established special loans for the
construction of the mines.
</P>
<P>
Mines in the key coal production counties, with 1.2 million
employees, generated 1.4 billion yuan in profits and 1.2 billion
yuan in taxes last year.
</P>
<P>
The ministry is determined to further reform the
management system of coal enterprises. Establishing a
shareholding company system is a main goal. More than 10,000
shareholding companies, or 35 percent of the total, have been
established in the key counties.
</P>
<P>
It will encourage mergers and cooperation between coal
producers. By 2000, every key coal producing county is expected
to create one or two coal groups whose assets are over 100 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Coal mines are also urged to enlarge their production scale and
to speed up technical renovation to improve the production and
decrease the pollution.
</P>
<P>
Implementing the coal law is a good way to regulate the
development of township and village mines, especially in key
counties. According to law, coal producers must apply for the mine
license and the production license from the government.
</P>
<P>
To date, 89 percent of coal producers in key counties have mine
licenses, 20 percentage points higher than the average level of
total township and village mines.
</P>
<P>
China has shut down more than 2,000 illegal private coal
mines. Last year, it produced 1.4 billion tons of coal last year,
ranking first in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
