<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0200 GMT September 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Jacques Poos, European Union (EU) term president and
foreign minister of Luxemburg, said here Monday Turkey has to
fulfill necessary conditions ahead of its EU membership
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission has earlier announced a report, known
as "Agenda 2000", excluding Turkey from the rank of prospective EU
membership candidates.
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- The Turkish police Monday arrested 12 people in
protest of the recently adopted eight-year compulsory education
law in Turkey's largest city of Istanbul.
</P>
<P>
They have been accused of stirring up a group of 150 Islamists
to attack the ATV, a leading Turkish television station, on Sunday
night, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The protesters stormed into the downtown television studio,
disarming a guard, smashing windows and television equipment. They
fled before anti-terror police arrived on the scene.
</P>
<P>
CASTRIES, ST. LUCIA -- The governments of the People's Republic
of China and Saint Lucia signed here Monday a joint communique on
the establishment of diplomatic relations, inaugurating a new
stage for developing bilateral ties in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Qin Huasun, Chinese Permanent Representative to the
United Nations, and George Odlum, Minister of Foreign Affairs and
International Trade of St. Lucia, put their signatures to the
communique on behalf of their respective governments. 
</P>
