<HEADLINE> Science and Technology And China's Economy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Industrial enterprises have become the major users of
scientific and technological research development. Large and
medium-sized businesses have enjoyed an annual average rise of 18
percent in technological development over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Spending on technological upgrading added up to 430 billion
yuan during the period, an average growth of nearly 23 percent
annually.
</P>
<P>
The successful launching of recoverable satellites, the
application of genetically engineered medicines, and some other
sophisticated developments have greatly helped the country's
high-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
During the Eighth Five-Year Plan, China saw an average annual
increase of 27 percent in high-tech foreign trade and had 31.9
billion US dollars of high-tech imports and exports in 1995, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Last year, China had more than 31,000 major scientific and
technological developments. And it received more than 100,000
patent applications, 20 percent of which came from abroad.
</P>
<P>
All these indicate that China is opening wider to the outside
world, that its investment environment is improving, and that it
is more attractive to overseas investors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
