<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pino Arlacchi Inaugurated as Head of U.N. Office at Geneva </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Pino Arlacchi of Italy was
inaugurated today as the director of the U.N. office in Vienna,
replacing his countryman Giorgio Giacomelli.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the inauguration ceremony were Hans
Blix, director-general of the International Atomic Energy Agency,
and Mauricio de Maria y Compos, director-general of the
U.N. Industrial Development Organization.
</P>
<P>
Arlacchi will also be in charge of a U.N. agency in Vienna
fighting against organized crime, drug trafficking and terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Arlacchi, a renowned expert on fighting the Italian Mafia,
said he is convinced that the world organization will gain victory
in the struggle against drug trafficking, organized crime and
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Arlacchi was appointed by U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan in
June to replace Giacomelli. Giacomelli had been in charge of the
office since 1991.  
</P>
</TEXT>
