<HEADLINE> Brazil's Second Nuclear Plant Will Open in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Nuclear Plant, Angra 2,
which is located in the state of Rio de Janeiro, will start
operations in 1998, said the National Commission of Nuclear Energy
(CNEN).
</P>
<P>
Angra 2 has the capacity to generate 1,300 megawatts of
electric power and will be an alternative to the thermonuclear
option for Brazil, said CNEN President Jose Mauro Esteves.
</P>
<P>
Esteves said the construction of nuclear plant Angra 1, which
is also located in Rio de Janeiro, has been completed.
</P>
<P>
Construction of a third plant, Angra 3, will be finished in
1999, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
