<HEADLINE> Biggest Chilean Business in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Corpora Guangzhou Ltd, Chile's
largest business in China, officially began production over the
weekend in Guangzhou Economic and Technological Development Zone,
Guangdong Province, "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean firm, which costs 10 million U.S. dollars, produces
beverages. It will employ 600 people and is expected to turn out
150 million liters a year.
</P>
<P>
Jorge Goles, CEO of Corpora Co, said "China is a popular place
in the Asia-Pacific region, and the Chinese Government places
special attention on attracting overseas investment to support its
economic growth."
</P>
<P>
According to Goles, also chairman and general manager of
Corpora Guangzhou Ltd., it took Corpora Guangzhou Ltd ten months
to market its products. Corpora beverages are now available in
five Chinese cities of Chengdu, Chongqing, Wuhan, Tianjin and
Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1893, Corpora has become a leading company in
South America. It has branches in America, Europe and Asia. Its
business scope includes food, light industry, tourism and
entertainment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
