<HEADLINE> Cuba, China Strengthening Economic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Economic relations between Cuba
and China are developing smoothly and will get much better, a
Cuban official said today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Vice Minister of Foreign
Investment and Economic Cooperation, Noemi Benitez, said that
China helps Cuba produce bicycles and electric fans, and is also
helping to construct energy and solar plants in Cuba.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 joint projects are developing well in Cuba,
especially in agriculture, fishery, health and biotechnology,
Benitez said.
</P>
<P>
She said that dozens of Chinese delegations have visited the
island looking for investments in tourism, the textile industry,
footwear, food and telecommunications. 
