<HEADLINE> Maradona Was framed: Agent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Diego Maradona, who
tested positive for cocaine last week, could have been framed, his
agent Guillermo Coppola told local television on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"It is so simple...a little drop, a glass of water or a sweet
containing the substance," Coppola said.
</P>
<P>
Coppola said Maradona, who is with the Argentine side Boca
Junior, had sworn to him that he had not taken cocaine.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine Football Association announced last Thursday that
he had failed a random drug test after scoring a penalty in his
first match of the new season for Boca Juniors.
</P>
<P>
If a second test confirmed the doping result, the 36-year old
hero would be suspended.
</P>
<P>
Maradona has twice received 15-month playing bans -- for using
cocaine when playing for Napoli in 1991 and for use of
performance-enhancing drugs at the 1994 World Cup in the United
States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
