<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Star
</P>
<P>
-- Former President Corazon Aquino and Manila Archbishop Jaime
Cardinal Sin will push through with the organizational meeting of
the Movement Against Revising the Charter this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Manila Standard
</P>
<P>
-- The Senate Monday approved on second reading the final phase
of the Comprehensive Tax Reform Program which effectively granted
159,900 pesos (5,330 U.S. dollars) in income tax exemption per
family.
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin
</P>
<P>
-- President Ramos Monday approved an eight percent
across-the-board increase in the monthly pensions of Social
Security System pensioners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
