<HEADLINE> Dutch Soccer Fans Jailed over Killing Rival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A Dutch court has jailed
eight Feyenoord Rotterdam soccer fans on Monday over their fatal
beating of a rival fan, a justice official said in Haarlem, the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Carlo Picornie, an Ajax Amsterdam fan, was clubbed to death in
March in a hooligans gangs clash outside Amsterdam.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 Feyenoord and Ajax supporters have appeared before
the court in Haarlem some 25 kilometers west of the capital.
</P>
<P>
A spokeswoman said the court had sentenced two of the accused
to four years imprisonment and another two to three and two years
in prison with six months suspended.
</P>
<P>
The four remaining supporters received up to 18 months in jail,
with up to six months suspended.
</P>
<P>
All were banned from attending soccer matches for two years and
ordered to pay damages to Picornie's partner.
</P>
<P>
Five Ajax supporters were jailed last week for their part in
the fight, each receiving six months imprisonment with two months
suspended. They too were barred from matches for two years.
</P>
<P>
Police investigations were continuing into the role of six more
Feyenoord supporters in the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
