<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Australian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Australian newspapers published today:
</P>
<P>
The Australian
</P>
<P>
-- A Royal funeral will be held on Saturday at Westminster
Abbey for Diana, Princess of Wales, and it will be one of the most
elaborate public tributes of modern times.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Morning Herald
</P>
<P>
-- The Australian federal government has shelved plans for a
shake-up of media ownership laws, effectively thwarting attempts
by media giant Kerry Packer to take over the Fairfax newspaper
group.
</P>
<P>
The Age
</P>
<P>
-- Before a silent Australian parliament, Prime Minister John
Howard spoke of the grief across the world over the loss of Diana,
a "beautiful, stylish woman" who had been committed to many causes
and captured the collective imagination.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- The Reserve Bank of Australia estimated that the economy
grew by just under 3 percent in 1996-1997 fisical year, with new
figures suggesting the housing recovery might have waned in recent
months.  
</P>
</TEXT>
