<HEADLINE> Hingis Enters Quarterfinals at U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Martina Hingis of
Switzerland beat Florencia Labat of Argentina 6-0, 6-2 Sunday to
reach the quarterfinals of the U.S. Open Tennis Championships at
Flushing, New York.
</P>
<P>
Hingis needed just 51 minutes to defeat Labat. She improved her
1997 record to 60-2. She has not dropped a set in this tournament.
</P>
<P>
Hingis will take on 10th seed Arantxa Sanchez Vicario who
advanced to the quarterfinals by bouncing Rachel Mcquillan of
Australia, 6-1, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In other fourth-round action, third seed Jana Novotna of the
Czech Republic defeated No. 12 Mary Joe Fernandez of the United
States, 7-5, 6- 4. She will face sixth seed Lindsay Davenport of
the United States who out play Magu Serna of Spain, 6-0, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Hard-serving Greg Rusedski of Britain earned a quarterfinal
berth by downing Czech Daniel Vacek, 7-6 (7-2), 6-2, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Pete Sampras of the United States, seeking a
record-tying fifth U.S. Open title, faced his toughest test of the
tournament against 15th seed Petr Korda of the Czech Republic.
</P>
</TEXT>
